DA Gerald Fox appeared for the State.  Defendant appeared in court, in custody, with Attorney Terrien.  Parties have the revocation and summary.  No changes or corrections.  Agreement to credit for 74 days.  State recommended:  9 months jail, all counts concurrent.  May serve on EMP.  May serve in Dane County if arrangements can be made.  Defense requesting 6 months on each count, concurrent.  EMP and Dane County.  

Court ordered:  7 months jail, each count concurrent.  May serve on Huber, according to jail rules.   May serve in Dane County, if arrangements can be made.  Credit for 75 days.  Judgment for unpaid court ordered financial obligations.
Sentencing hearing on revocation on September 28, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
with attached revocation summary.  Copy sent to Judge electronically 9/7.
from DOC

ADA Melissa Inlow appears for the State.  Defendant appeared in person and with Attorney Betthauser.  Amended information filed with court.  Reading of the amended information waived.  Defendant plead  no contest to all counts in the amended information.  Joint recommendation for 3 year probation.  Maintain employment.  Obtain HSED or GED.  Pay CS and pay on arrears.  Court recited the charges and possible penalties she plead to.  Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant.  He understood. Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the pleas.  Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights. Court found that a factual basis exists for the pleas.  Found guilty of counts 1-5.  Defendant did not exercise his right to allocution.  Attorney Betthauser asks that some court costs be waived.   Court ordered sentence withheld,  3 years probation.  Maintain employment, not to terminate without agent's approval.  Work towards obtaining HSED or GED.  Pay current child support order and as amended from time to time.  Pay on arrears.   Set up payment plan.   The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.  CC on counts 1-3.  No costs on counts 4 and 5.
